    <refsection id="Description_MMR_IdealGear">
        <title>Description</title>
        <para>
            This block is an ideal gear without inertia, but with bearing. The relationship between angular velocities is:
        </para>
        <para>
            <latex>
                \begin{eqnarray}
                \omega_A - \omega_{bearing} = ratio * (\omega_B - \omega_{bearing})
                \end{eqnarray}
            </latex>
        </para>
        <para>
            with <latex>\omega_A\:</latex> (resp. <latex>\omega_B\:</latex>) is the angular velocity of input wheel (resp. output wheel).
        </para>
    </refsection>
